it.emarolab.owloop.core

Interface DataProperty.Disjoint<O,J,D extends DataProperty<O,J>>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the type of ontology in which the axioms for classes will be applied.
    J - the type of the described data property (it also represents the type of Semantic.Axioms managed by this Descriptor.
    D - the type of the DataProperty descriptor instantiated during buildDisjointDataProperty() through getNewDisjointDataProperty(Object, Object).
    All Superinterfaces:
    DataProperty<O,J>, Semantic, Semantic.Descriptor<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MORDataProperty.Disjoint<D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MORDefinitionDataProperty, MORFullDataProperty
    Enclosing interface:
    DataProperty<O,J>

    public static interface DataProperty.Disjoint<O,J,D extends DataProperty<O,J>>
extends DataProperty<O,J>
    The Semantic.Descriptor for disjointed data properties.

    This Semantic.Descriptor synchronises the disjointed data properties of this property (i.e.: the Ground#getGroundInstance()).

      • readSemantic

        default java.util.List<Semantic.MappingIntent> readSemantic()
        Description copied from interface: Semantic.Descriptor
        This method is used to synchronise specific Semantic.Axioms (or Semantic.SemanticAxioms) from the ontology. It manipulates the OWLLOOP representation to be equal to the queried OWL structure. It is based on Axioms#synchroniseFrom(Axioms).
        Specified by:
        readSemantic in interface Semantic.Descriptor<O,J>
        Returns:
        the changes made in the Semantic.Axioms during the reading. Those objects may not have the Semantic.MappingIntent.getOntologyChanges() field initialised (i.e.: Void).

      • synchroniseDisjointDataPropertyToSemantic

        default Semantic.Axioms.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseDisjointDataPropertyToSemantic()
        It calls Semantic.Axioms#synchroniseTo(Axioms) with queryDisjointDataProperty() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed in the OWL representation for synchronise it with respect to getDisjointDataProperty(). This should be done by Semantic.Descriptor.writeSemantic().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise this structure with the disjoint properties of Semantic.Descriptor.getInstance(); to the OWL representation.

      • synchroniseDisjointDataPropertyFromSemantic

        default Semantic.Axioms.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseDisjointDataPropertyFromSemantic()
        It calls SemanticAxioms#synchroniseFrom(Axioms) with queryDisjointDataProperty() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed into the getDisjointDataProperty() in order to synchronise it with respect to an OWL representation. This is be done by readSemantic().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise the disjoint data properties of Semantic.Descriptor.getInstance(); from an OWL representation to this Descriptor.
